00:23:53.620 --> 00:23:59.590
Now, the third part of the new
Android search experience is

00:23:59.590 --> 00:24:01.650
called Google Now.

00:24:01.650 --> 00:24:03.810
Today's smartphones
are powerful.

00:24:03.810 --> 00:24:05.460
They can do pretty much
anything you ask.

00:24:05.460 --> 00:24:07.610
Search the web, give
you directions,

00:24:07.610 --> 00:24:09.820
traffic info, anything.

00:24:09.820 --> 00:24:13.160
But smartphones are only as
smart as you tell them to be.

00:24:13.160 --> 00:24:15.330
They rely on you to
do everything.

00:24:15.330 --> 00:24:17.660
You have to enter a search
query, you have to type in a

00:24:17.660 --> 00:24:20.620
street address, and you have
to ask for traffic in a

00:24:20.620 --> 00:24:22.170
particular area.

00:24:22.170 --> 00:24:25.700
But with Google Now, that
starts to change.

00:24:25.700 --> 00:24:28.540
Google Now gets you just the
right information at just the

00:24:28.540 --> 00:24:29.660
right time.

00:24:29.660 --> 00:24:32.260
And all of it happens
automatically.

00:24:32.260 --> 00:24:34.060
So how do we do this?

00:24:34.060 --> 00:24:37.190
If you choose to, Google Now
uses things like your search

00:24:37.190 --> 00:24:40.140
history, your location history,
and your calendar to

00:24:40.140 --> 00:24:44.090
figure out what information
you might need and when.

00:24:44.090 --> 00:24:46.640
Let's see a few examples
on slides.

00:24:46.640 --> 00:24:47.840
Traffic.

00:24:47.840 --> 00:24:50.810
Google Now figures out
when you commute from

00:24:50.810 --> 00:24:54.010
home to work and back.

00:24:54.010 --> 00:24:56.250
It'll then tell you how long
the commute on your usual

00:24:56.250 --> 00:24:57.500
route is going to be.

00:24:57.500 --> 00:24:59.770
And it'll give you
a faster route if

00:24:59.770 --> 00:25:02.220
there's a lot of traffic.

00:25:02.220 --> 00:25:04.270
Next, public transit.

00:25:04.270 --> 00:25:07.500
When you're near a bus stop or
on a platform at a subway

00:25:07.500 --> 00:25:11.010
station, Google Now tells you
when the next bus or train

00:25:11.010 --> 00:25:12.260
will arrive.

00:25:18.960 --> 00:25:20.730
Places.

00:25:20.730 --> 00:25:23.520
Google Now will show you bars,
restaurants, and places of

00:25:23.520 --> 00:25:26.760
interest around you as you
walk down the street.

00:25:26.760 --> 00:25:28.620
And when you're in a restaurant
trying to figure

00:25:28.620 --> 00:25:31.500
out what to order, Google Now
will tell you what that

00:25:31.500 --> 00:25:35.430
restaurant is best known for.

00:25:35.430 --> 00:25:36.940
Next, appointment.

00:25:36.940 --> 00:25:39.260
When you have a calendar event,
Google Now will help

00:25:39.260 --> 00:25:41.560
you get there on time.

00:25:41.560 --> 00:25:45.520
For example, if you normally
take the bus to get around,

00:25:45.520 --> 00:25:48.510
Google Now will tell you when
to leave based on how long

00:25:48.510 --> 00:25:51.890
it'll take you to walk to the
bus stop, when the next bus

00:25:51.890 --> 00:25:55.520
arrives, and how long that bus
ride will take, so you get

00:25:55.520 --> 00:25:56.770
there on time.

00:26:01.570 --> 00:26:02.790
Flights.

00:26:02.790 --> 00:26:05.720
If you have an upcoming flight
that you've searched for,

00:26:05.720 --> 00:26:08.390
Google Now keeps you up
to date on the status.

00:26:08.390 --> 00:26:11.600
It tells you which terminal to
go to, and it updates you if

00:26:11.600 --> 00:26:13.425
there's a delay, all
automatically.

00:26:18.080 --> 00:26:18.690
Sports.

