01:17:45.820 --> 01:17:49.450
coming to the Android
smartphone

01:17:49.450 --> 01:17:51.230
today in Android Play.

01:17:51.230 --> 01:17:52.590
It's also available
for your phone.

01:17:52.590 --> 01:17:53.840
So enjoy that.

01:17:56.780 --> 01:17:59.900
Now we have one more Google+
announcement today.

01:17:59.900 --> 01:18:02.730
And it goes back to really why
we started the project in the

01:18:02.730 --> 01:18:07.540
first place, to really bring
real-life sharing to software.

01:18:07.540 --> 01:18:10.360
Think about the time that you
spend with the people that you

01:18:10.360 --> 01:18:13.830
love, your family, your
best friends.

01:18:13.830 --> 01:18:16.690
Think about where you spend
that time with them.

01:18:16.690 --> 01:18:18.420
It's likely at a barbecue, a

01:18:18.420 --> 01:18:21.270
restaurant, a picnic, a wedding.

01:18:21.270 --> 01:18:25.350
The common theme here is that
these are all events.

01:18:25.350 --> 01:18:28.280
Events have a wonderful way
to bring people together.

01:18:28.280 --> 01:18:32.330
They allow you to create and
share cherished moments.

01:18:32.330 --> 01:18:36.090
Yet unfortunately, the substance
of a real-world

01:18:36.090 --> 01:18:38.920
event is lost online.

01:18:38.920 --> 01:18:42.110
Just consider the state of
today's online tools.

01:18:42.110 --> 01:18:45.530
Online event tools basically are
glorified web forums that

01:18:45.530 --> 01:18:47.450
ask you, are you going?

01:18:47.450 --> 01:18:48.750
Yes or no.

01:18:48.750 --> 01:18:50.820
They kind of help you
manage who you're

01:18:50.820 --> 01:18:52.460
inviting to the party.

01:18:52.460 --> 01:18:54.650
But what happens when
the party starts?

01:18:54.650 --> 01:18:56.760
Well, what about after
the party?

01:18:56.760 --> 01:19:00.800
Today's online tools bail when
you need them the most.

01:19:00.800 --> 01:19:03.690
In life, we plan, we party,
we keep in touch.

01:19:03.690 --> 01:19:06.660
We think software should make
all of that more awesome

01:19:06.660 --> 01:19:10.160
before, during, and
after your event.

01:19:10.160 --> 01:19:13.880
That's why today we're so
excited to be announcing

01:19:13.880 --> 01:19:15.320
Google+ Events.

01:19:19.020 --> 01:19:21.730
Now, for the next few moments,
I'm going to show you how you

01:19:21.730 --> 01:19:23.970
can use Google+ Events
before, during, and

01:19:23.970 --> 01:19:25.670
after your next party.

01:19:25.670 --> 01:19:27.550
Let's start off with before.

01:19:27.550 --> 01:19:31.350
Now, perhaps the most important
thing we do is

01:19:31.350 --> 01:19:32.700
invite someone.

01:19:32.700 --> 01:19:36.340
When you invite someone to your
home, or to a wedding, or

01:19:36.340 --> 01:19:39.560
even to your favorite
restaurant, that's a deeply

01:19:39.560 --> 01:19:41.080
intimate act.

01:19:41.080 --> 01:19:44.580
You're handpicking who's going
to be in the room.

01:19:44.580 --> 01:19:47.110
So we think that who you're
inviting should

01:19:47.110 --> 01:19:48.910
feel special too.

01:19:48.910 --> 01:19:52.310
And so that's why we've designed
a product to offer

01:19:52.310 --> 01:19:55.600
lots of ways to send absolutely
beautiful

01:19:55.600 --> 01:19:59.130
invitations in something we
call cinemagraphic themes.

01:19:59.130 --> 01:20:00.720
I'll show you that
in a moment.

01:20:00.720 --> 01:20:03.150
We also understand that you
need to manage the entire

01:20:03.150 --> 01:20:06.250
process, and we've built in
great management tools,

01:20:06.250 --> 01:20:09.820
including deep integration
with Google Calendar.

01:20:09.820 --> 01:20:11.430
Let's just show you.

01:20:11.430 --> 01:20:16.130
Matt, here, is going to invite
some friends to a brunch.

01:20:16.130 --> 01:20:17.490
Wait till we switch to demo.

01:20:20.780 --> 01:20:22.200
So Matt's going to
use the product.

01:20:22.200 --> 01:20:24.460
He is going to click on the
Calendar button there

01:20:24.460 --> 01:20:25.600
in the Share box.

01:20:25.600 --> 01:20:28.180
And he's going to now start
inviting people to a brunch in

01:20:28.180 --> 01:20:29.440
Half Moon Bay.

01:20:29.440 --> 01:20:31.200
It's a city about 30
miles from here.

01:20:31.200 --> 01:20:33.260
It happens to be his hometown.

01:20:33.260 --> 01:20:35.960
And he'll fill in some
basic information.

01:20:35.960 --> 01:20:38.000
Now he'll choose a theme.

01:20:38.000 --> 01:20:40.080
Now here's where it gets
really amazing.

01:20:40.080 --> 01:20:44.390
We have over two dozen of
these cinemagraphs,

01:20:44.390 --> 01:20:47.070
beautifully animated themes.

01:20:47.070 --> 01:20:49.670
You may not be able to see the
subtle animation in the

01:20:49.670 --> 01:20:52.010
audience, but some of these
are just amazing.

01:20:52.010 --> 01:20:52.745
Lights flicker.

01:20:52.745 --> 01:20:53.980
You can see the barbecue.

01:20:53.980 --> 01:20:55.290
That's one of my favorites.

01:20:55.290 --> 01:20:58.770
And we really professionally
built some amazing ways to

01:20:58.770 --> 01:21:01.120
make your guests feel special.

01:21:01.120 --> 01:21:04.230
Now, since this is a beach
brunch, why don't you pick a

01:21:04.230 --> 01:21:05.400
beach theme?

01:21:05.400 --> 01:21:07.760
And he'll go ahead
and set that.

01:21:07.760 --> 01:21:11.650
Now, finally, Matt will add
guests whether or not they're

01:21:11.650 --> 01:21:12.860
on Google+.

01:21:12.860 --> 01:21:16.560
He just adds their emails, and
then he sends the invitation.

01:21:16.560 --> 01:21:18.940
Now let's see what it's like
to receive the invitation.

01:21:18.940 --> 01:21:20.460
In this case, we're
going to switch.

01:21:20.460 --> 01:21:23.720
We're going to pretend to be
Lindsay, one of Matt's

01:21:23.720 --> 01:21:25.340
imaginary friends.

01:21:25.340 --> 01:21:28.810
Yes, he has lots of imaginary
friends still.

01:21:28.810 --> 01:21:32.870
Now, from Lindsay's viewpoint,
she gets this beautiful event

01:21:32.870 --> 01:21:34.120
post in the stream.

01:21:34.120 --> 01:21:38.380
And when she hovers over that,
it unfolds just like you might

01:21:38.380 --> 01:21:41.460
with an invitation you
received in the mail.

01:21:41.460 --> 01:21:44.420
Lindsay can check her schedule
right from the post with

01:21:44.420 --> 01:21:45.950
Calendar integration.

01:21:45.950 --> 01:21:47.860
And she can see that
she's free.

01:21:47.860 --> 01:21:50.270
And so she'll say, yes,
that she's going.

01:21:50.270 --> 01:21:52.730
Now if you jump over to
Lindsay's calendar, a

01:21:52.730 --> 01:21:56.420
brand-new feature in Google
Calendar, first, the social

01:21:56.420 --> 01:21:58.380
event has been added.

01:21:58.380 --> 01:22:00.370
Matt's photo is in the corner.

01:22:00.370 --> 01:22:03.210
And if she clicks on that,
she gets that beautiful

01:22:03.210 --> 01:22:05.140
cinemagraph integrated
right in.

01:22:05.140 --> 01:22:05.630
Isn't that awesome?

01:22:05.630 --> 01:22:10.840
[APPLAUSE]

01:22:10.840 --> 01:22:12.950
VIC GUNDOTRA: She can even see
the beautiful faces of her

01:22:12.950 --> 01:22:14.360
friends who are going.

01:22:14.360 --> 01:22:17.510
All of these small details, we
think, help set the mood for

01:22:17.510 --> 01:22:20.960
your event, the right mood
right from the start.

01:22:20.960 --> 01:22:23.130
Now finally, we can
click through into

01:22:23.130 --> 01:22:25.380
the event page detail.

01:22:25.380 --> 01:22:29.280
And there, once again, Lindsay
can pull down on the invite,

01:22:29.280 --> 01:22:30.880
get that beautiful experience.

01:22:30.880 --> 01:22:33.180
She can see updates
from the host.

01:22:33.180 --> 01:22:34.320
She can see photos.

01:22:34.320 --> 01:22:36.490
She can see who else is going.

01:22:36.490 --> 01:22:39.830
Let's go back to slides.

01:22:39.830 --> 01:22:42.230
So we think that the combination
of cinemagraphs,

01:22:42.230 --> 01:22:44.960
Calendar integration, those
other things that we showed

01:22:44.960 --> 01:22:48.300
you really make it both a
beautiful and a useful way for

01:22:48.300 --> 01:22:49.570
you to manage your party.

01:22:49.570 --> 01:22:52.190
But that's just before
the event.

01:22:52.190 --> 01:22:55.280
Now let's talk about
during the event.

01:22:55.280 --> 01:22:57.220
Now, it's no surprise that
during the event,

01:22:57.220 --> 01:22:58.520
photos are a big deal.

01:22:58.520 --> 01:23:02.130
Just taking a photo causes
people to smile and laugh.

01:23:02.130 --> 01:23:05.310
They help us relive the
event when it's over.

01:23:05.310 --> 01:23:07.740
But you know what
the problem is.

01:23:07.740 --> 01:23:10.590
Today, with the proliferation
of devices and smartphones,

01:23:10.590 --> 01:23:13.000
everyone's photos get lost.

01:23:13.000 --> 01:23:15.160
They're with all the guests,
and they never,

01:23:15.160 --> 01:23:16.550
ever come back together.

01:23:16.550 --> 01:23:19.880
So no one can enjoy
them in one spot.

01:23:19.880 --> 01:23:23.440
With Google+ Events, we have a
groundbreaking feature, my

01:23:23.440 --> 01:23:24.940
favorite feature
of the product.

01:23:24.940 --> 01:23:28.760
And it's called Party Mode, and
it fixes those problems.

01:23:28.760 --> 01:23:32.090
Once you've enabled Party Mode
on your device, all new photos

01:23:32.090 --> 01:23:35.680
automatically get added to
the event in real time.

01:23:35.680 --> 01:23:39.190
As more and more guests turn
on Party Mode, all those

01:23:39.190 --> 01:23:41.410
photos instantly appear.

01:23:41.410 --> 01:23:43.970
In this way, Google+
Events gives your

01:23:43.970 --> 01:23:46.230
party a visual pulse.

01:23:46.230 --> 01:23:49.260
We've even added a live slide
show that you can show during

01:23:49.260 --> 01:23:50.720
the event to make it fun.

01:23:50.720 --> 01:23:52.450
Let's show you.

01:23:52.450 --> 01:23:55.150
Let's go back to demo.

01:23:55.150 --> 01:23:56.840
Matt's obviously in the mood.

01:23:56.840 --> 01:23:58.380
His brunch has already
started.

01:23:58.380 --> 01:24:02.950
Now, because it's already
started, Android knows that

01:24:02.950 --> 01:24:04.280
this is the correct time.

01:24:04.280 --> 01:24:06.630
And it sends him this
notification.

01:24:06.630 --> 01:24:11.290
Now, at Matt's discretion, he
can choose with one click to

01:24:11.290 --> 01:24:15.000
take that first photo and
turn on Party Mode.

01:24:15.000 --> 01:24:15.700
Go ahead, Matt.

01:24:15.700 --> 01:24:16.280
Take your picture.

01:24:16.280 --> 01:24:17.650
All right, very good.

01:24:17.650 --> 01:24:21.840
Now, if you note at the top,
the green icon stays there.

01:24:21.840 --> 01:24:24.790
So you always know when
Party Mode is on.

01:24:24.790 --> 01:24:28.210
And as guests turn this on, they
can control the settings

01:24:28.210 --> 01:24:29.630
right there in Notifications.

01:24:29.630 --> 01:24:33.150
Let's go back to the Events
landing page.

01:24:33.150 --> 01:24:36.520
Now, on the Events landing page,
you get to see all the

01:24:36.520 --> 01:24:38.030
photos stream in.

01:24:38.030 --> 01:24:40.740
People who are at the event who
