01:41:29.670 --> 01:41:32.230
talk about some of the design
philosophy that has gone into

01:41:32.230 --> 01:41:33.690
this device.

01:41:33.690 --> 01:41:34.940
ISABELLE OLSSON: Thank you.

01:41:42.400 --> 01:41:46.490
So we created Glass so that
you can interact with the

01:41:46.490 --> 01:41:49.220
virtual world without
distracting you

01:41:49.220 --> 01:41:51.320
from the real world.

01:41:51.320 --> 01:41:55.050
And one clear example of this is
that we decided to actually

01:41:55.050 --> 01:41:58.190
position the display
above your eye.

01:41:58.190 --> 01:42:01.540
And Glass as a whole is designed
to be close to your

01:42:01.540 --> 01:42:03.840
senses, but not blocking them.

01:42:10.150 --> 01:42:13.860
And this picture shows so
clearly how we don't want

01:42:13.860 --> 01:42:16.460
technology to get in the way.

01:42:16.460 --> 01:42:19.670
The baby looks into
the Mom's eyes.

01:42:19.670 --> 01:42:21.090
They connect.

01:42:21.090 --> 01:42:24.410
And while doing that, she can
capture this beautiful moment

01:42:24.410 --> 01:42:25.660
without any distractions.

01:42:28.210 --> 01:42:33.530
And whether it's with family or
friends, we want to empower

01:42:33.530 --> 01:42:38.760
people to use technology
naturally, like in this moment

01:42:38.760 --> 01:42:40.010
of celebration.

01:42:45.630 --> 01:42:50.480
So we wanted to pack all this
amazing technology into this

01:42:50.480 --> 01:42:54.600
product to let you do amazing
things with it.

01:42:54.600 --> 01:42:58.110
But that's also a slight
conflict, through that if this

01:42:58.110 --> 01:43:03.920
is not ridiculously light, it
doesn't belong on your face.

01:43:03.920 --> 01:43:07.790
And we didn't only want to make
it physically light, but

01:43:07.790 --> 01:43:09.920
also visually light.

01:43:09.920 --> 01:43:12.360
We don't want to compete too
much with the user's own

01:43:12.360 --> 01:43:15.490
individuality, so no superfluous
detailing.

01:43:15.490 --> 01:43:20.230
And we really tried to reduce
it to its core essence.

01:43:20.230 --> 01:43:24.740
And one of the results of this
is that our latest prototype

01:43:24.740 --> 01:43:27.560
