01:54:20.120 --> 01:54:21.170
presentation.

01:54:21.170 --> 01:54:23.820
I wasn't really expecting
it to.

01:54:23.820 --> 01:54:27.230
But I wanted to tell you, well,
you've seen a whole

01:54:27.230 --> 01:54:28.010
bunch of stuff.

01:54:28.010 --> 01:54:30.130
I'm personally really excited
about Glass in

01:54:30.130 --> 01:54:31.290
my day-to-day usage.

01:54:31.290 --> 01:54:34.220
I've had moments with
family like that.

01:54:34.220 --> 01:54:36.090
And there are all kinds
of things this

01:54:36.090 --> 01:54:38.620
can capture and share.

01:54:38.620 --> 01:54:44.420
But obviously, capturing images,
videos, even sharing

01:54:44.420 --> 01:54:48.250
video, that's only a part
of what a wearable

01:54:48.250 --> 01:54:49.630
computer can do.

01:54:49.630 --> 01:54:53.430
And we've highlighted a few
other little things here.

01:54:53.430 --> 01:54:57.840
But why are we showing
you basically

01:54:57.840 --> 01:54:59.520
this kind of utility?

